Distribution. The species has been recorded from the Indian Ocean to west Pacific Ocean. Indian Ocean: Indonesia ( Trilles 2008 ), India ( Pillai 1954 ; Bruce & Bowman 1989 ; Trilles et al. 2011), South Africa ( Schiöedte & Meinert 1883 ; Stebbing 1908–1910 ; Barnard 1924–1926 ; 1940; Bruce & Bowman 1989 ), Mozambique ( Nierstrasz 1931 ; Bruce & Bowman 1989 ) and Red Sea (
Hadfield et al. 2014b
). Pacific Ocean: Northern Australia and Western Irian Jaya ( Bruce & Bowman 1989 ).

Hosts. Known only from the family Hemiramphidae : Halfbeak fish
Hemirhamphus far (Forsskål, 1775)
(Barnard 1924–1926 ; Pillai 1954 ; Kensley 1978 ; Bruce & Bowman 1989 ;
Hadfield et al. 2014b
) and
Hemirhamphus robustus Günther, 1866
( Bruce & Bowman 1989 ;
Hadfield et al. 2014b
).
